CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 13, 1941, pg. 2 reads: "Entire Community Pays Last Respects To Al Jackson - Impressive ceremonies marked the final rites for Alter Jackson, young businessman, who was drowned during Labor Day weekend. Picture here shows procession taking body from home to hearse.- Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Men, and women holding flowers, gathered beside Clyde C. Davis funeral home hearse, and Jackson house, for funeral of Alter Jackson, another version
